record_data.record_plain_text: I. GENERAL This tariff sets forth the terms, conditions of service and rates for reliability services to be supplied by PSEG Energy Resources & Trade LLC (???PSEG ER&T???) to PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (???PJM???) pursuant to Sections 119 and 121 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff (???PJM Tariff???). Definitions: Unless otherwise defined, capitalized terms used herein shall have the meaning set forth in the PJM Tariff.

record_data.record_plain_text:
IV. COST OF SERVICE RECOVERY RATE
The formulas and values used to compute the monthly Cost of Service Recovery Rate for the Units are set forth in Equation A-1 below:
Equation A-1
Monthly Cost of Service Recovery Rate = greater of 0 or Monthly Availability Payment + Monthly Project Investment Tracker Payment _ Actual Net Revenues for the Month
If the Monthly Cost of Service Recovery Rate is a negative amount, the absolute value shall be credited to the unamortized balance of Project Investments in that month.
Section 1. Monthly Availability Payment. The Monthly Availability Payment is calculated in accordance with Equation A-2 below: Equation A-2 Monthly Availability Payment ($)
= Annual Fixed Revenue Requirements ($) / 12
Where: The Annual Fixed Revenue Requirement for Sewaren, Units No. 1, 2, 3 and 4 is $18,987,592 and the Annual Fixed Revenue Requirement for Hudson, Unit No. 1 is $14,512,408. Section 2. Monthly Project Investment Tracker Payment. The Monthly Project Investment Tracker Payment is calculated in accordance with Equation A-3 below:
Equation A-3 Monthly Project Investment Tracker Payment ($)
= Unamortized Project Investment Tracker Costs ($) / The Total Number of Months or Portions of a Month That Remain During the Term of this Tariff
The balance in Unamortized Project Investment costs shall accrue carrying charges at 12.46% per annum and shall be increased for actual Project Investment costs incurred in each month. For the purposes of this equation, the Term of this Tariff shall be the Term specified under Section III hereof as modified from time to time. Project Investments costs for 2005 shall not exceed $15.6 million. D. For Project Investments planned for 2006, PSEG ER&T shall file with the Commission for informational purposes, a list of planned Project Investments and costs, with appropriate support, by no later than October 7, 2005. For Project Investments planned for 2007 and any subsequent years that this tariff remains in effect, PSEG ER&T shall file with the Commission for informational purposes, a list of planned Project Investments and costs, with appropriate support, by no later than October 1 of the previous year. Parties may object to the planned Project Investments or costs under Section 206 of the Federal Power Act; provided however, that PSEG ER&T shall be obligated to undertake construction of only those Project Investment(s) to which objections do not apply and further provided that PSEG ER&T shall not be deemed to have acted inconsistently with the Performance Standards under Section 121 of the PJM Tariff due to any delay or deferment of the Projected Investment(s) which are the subject of such Federal Power Act Section 206 proceeding. E. Project Investment Tracker costs shall be recovered on the basis of actual costs incurred, with carrying charges as set forth in paragraph A. No later than March 31 of the following year (or if at the end of the Term, within ninety (90) days of such date), PSEG ER&T will submit a report to PJM showing the actual amounts expended for the Project Investments during the previous year. Any dispute between PSEG ER&T and PJM concerning the amounts of any such costs shall be subject to the dispute resolution procedure set forth in the PJM Tariff. F. Refund of Project Investment Reimbursement: With respect to each Unit, PSEG ER&T shall refund PJM a prorata share of the amount of each Project Investment for which it received reimbursement under this Tariff as set forth herein. The Refund of Project Investment Reimbursement shall be determined using the following formula: Monthly Refund of Project Investment Reimbursement Amount = The amount of the Project Investment/100.8 months Where: Each monthly payment for a Project Investment made by PJM to PSEG ER&T shall be considered a separate Project Investment for the purposes of the Refund of Project Investment Reimbursement calculation and each such Project Investment shall be deemed to have been placed in-service on the first day of the month following the month to which the Project Investment monthly payment is attributable. With respect to each Project Investment, during the period beginning on the date that PJM determined that the Unit could deactivate and ending 100.8 months following the in-service date for such Project Investment, PSEG ER&T shall make the Refund of Project Investment Reimbursement to PJM each month for every month in which the Unit operates. Such amounts shall be credited to transmission customers on the same basis as costs are allocated under Section 120 of the PJM Tariff. The months the Unit operates past the date PJM determines it could deactivate need not be continuous, and the Refund of Project Investment Reimbursement will continue regardless of ownership of the Unit. Upon retirement and demolition of any Unit, PSEG ER&T will refund to PJM all salvage payments received in connection with Project Investments net of any associated salvage costs. In the event that any Project Investment facilities are utilized by PSEG ER&T or any affiliate in other generating units, PSEG ER&T shall refund to PJM the fair market value of such facilities at the time of deployment, net of any associated transfer or salvage costs. Section 3: Actual Net Revenues: Actual Net Revenues are all revenues from PJM markets and unit-specific bilateral contracts (including without limitation revenues for sales of energy, capacity and ancillary services) net of the marginal cost of service for energy sales equal to the amount of Unit offer caps for energy sales into the PJM Interchange Energy Market determined in accordance with the methodology specified in Section 6.4.2(a)(ii) of the PJM Tariff., In the event that Unforced Capacity (or any successor measurement of the capacity value of Capacity Resources) is not sold under a unit-specific bilateral contract, the value of each unit of such Unforced Capacity shall be determined as follows. For the period from February 25, 2005 until December 28, 2005, the value of the Unforced Capacity shall be based on clearing price in PJM???s daily Capacity Credit Market. Beginning on December 29, 2005, the value of capacity per month shall be based on the weighted average of the values for Unforced Capacity as determined in the Unforced Capacity auctions conducted by PJM with weighting as follows: 60% by the clearing prices realized in each of the three PJM interval auctions (20% weighting for each interval auction); 30% by the clearing prices realized in each of the three most current PJM monthly auctions (10% weighting for each monthly auction); and 10% by the clearing prices realized in the PJM daily auction for each day of a given month, or such other weighting as PJM may advise to PSEG ER&T with at least four months??? advance written notice; provided that the weighting valuation methodology shall be phased-in to be consistent with the availability of the identified term auctions commencing on December 29, 2005. In calculating Actual Net Revenues, if a Unit experiences a Forced Outage for any time period it was bid into the PJM Energy Exchange Market and accepted by PJM, the profits or losses associated with purchases made by PSEG ER&T in the PJM real-time market to cover generation short-falls associated with Forced Outage of the Unit shall be included. Section 4: Material Change in Circumstances: Should the methodology for determination of the offer caps under Section 6.4.2(a)(ii) of the PJM Tariff change during the Term or in the event of any other material change during the Term in circumstances affecting the cost of service or costs of Project Investments for the Units, PSEG ER&T shall be entitled to initiate an application under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act to modify the rates set forth herein.

record_data.record_plain_text: NATURE OF SERVICE During the Term of this tariff, PSEG ER&T shall cause PSEG Fossil LLC to continue operating the following units (???the Units???) located in the PJM region: Sewaren, Unit No. 1 Sewaren, Unit No. 2 Sewaren, Unit No. 3 Sewaren, Unit No. 4 Hudson, Unit No. 1. The Units will be operated in accordance with the Performance Standards set forth in Section 121 of the PJM Tariff. PJM???s sole remedies against PSEG ER&T for any default under this tariff shall be as specified in such provision. Except when the Units are unavailable due to a Forced Outage or Planned Outage, each Unit will be bid into the day-ahead and real-time PJM Energy Interchange Markets by PSEG ER&T at rates equal to the Unit offer caps for energy sales into the PJM Interchange Energy Market determined in accordance with the methodology specified in Section 6.4.2(a)(ii) of the PJM Tariff. The Units will not be de-listed as Capacity Resources for PJM. PJM shall pay PSEG ER&T the amounts set forth in Article IV hereof as Cost of Service Recovery Rates.

record_data.record_plain_text: TERM Subject to the other parts of this paragraph 1 and paragraph 2 of this Section III, this tariff shall remain in effect for as long as PJM determines that the Units or any particular Unit or Units are needed for reliability purposes. PJM has determined that the Units will be needed until September 1, 2008 as to the Sewaren Units Nos. 1-4 and until December 7, 2011 as to the Hudson Unit No. 1 upon which dates the Term will end as to the respective unit(s). PSEG ER&T will provide reliability services beyond these dates (or any other date to which this tariff is subsequently extended) provided that PJM provides at least one-hundred and twenty (120) days advance written notice prior to such termination date advising that the Units or any particular Unit will continue to be needed for reliability purposes and setting forth a new date of termination. In the event that PJM provides written notice to PSEG ER&T that the Units or any particular Unit or Units will be needed for reliability purposes for any period beyond September 1, 2008 (or any other date of extension), PSEG ER&T shall, within sixty (60) days of the receipt of such written notice, file an amendment to this tariff reflecting the modified Term. 2. This tariff shall terminate as to any Unit(s) that PJM determines are no longer needed for reliability purposes following one hundred and twenty (120) days written notice to PSEG ER&T of such determination; provided however, that to the extent that PSEG ER&T is recovering Project Investment costs with respect to the Unit(s) which are the subject of the PJM notice, PSEG ER&T shall be entitled to recover, over the remaining Term of this tariff, all of such Project Investment costs that have been incurred as of the date PSEG ER&T receives such written notice. In the event that PJM???s notice advises that a particular Unit or Units are no longer needed for reliability purposes but that other Unit(s) are still needed for reliability purposes, PSEG ER&T shall, within thirty (30) days of the receipt of such notice, file to modify this tariff to reflect the removal of such Unit(s). PSEG ER&T shall be entitled, without seeking or receiving any further approvals from PJM, to retire any Unit(s) determined by PJM to be no longer needed for reliability purposes. 3. In the event of a Forced Outage with respect to any Unit(s), PSEG ER&T shall notify PJM, within thirty (30) days of the commencement of such Forced Outage, of the nature, expected duration and projected level of expenditures in Project Investment(s) (if any) to effect repairs. If Projects Investment(s) are required, within not more than thirty (30) days of its receipt of such notice, PJM shall advise PSEG ER&T whether it is willing to authorize such Project Investment(s) in addition to the Project Investments identified in the filing provided under Section IV D hereof. If PJM determines not to authorize additional Project Investments or costs under Section 206 of the Federal Power Act; provided however, that PSEG ER&T shall be obligated to undertake construction of only those Project Investment(s) to which objections do not apply and further provided that PSEG ER&T shall not be deemed to have acted inconsistently with the Performance Standards under Section 121 of the PJM Tariff due to any delay or deferment of the Projected Investment(s) which are the subject of such Federal Power Act Section 206 proceeding.
